26/09/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police searched the homes and offices of alleged supporters of war crimes indictees and detained four people Thursday (23 September), said Interior Ministry spokesman Zlatko Mehun. He added that the four -- believed to be close aides to fugitive General Ante Gotovina -- were interrogated and released Friday afternoon. Deputy Police Chief Jakov Bukvic identified the four as Zeljko Dilber, Ante Zoni Maksan, Zdenko Rincic and Zeljko Matozan. Officials have not yet decided whether to press charges against them. (HIC, AP - 24/09/04)
